n a booking is made for a room that is affected by it - rather than to wait for a complaint before acting upon it. I was very disappointed that a 5 star hotel would take bookings in this manner, without prior warning.Overall, a nice hotel - and the food is excellent. However, I think the awarded 5 stars are for the cuisine, and not for the rooms. I've stayed in better 4 stars, I have travelled extensively, and never before experienced builders outside of my window in the early hours of the morning! OK, we had one night refunded which was a fair gesture, but I'd have preferred the whole experience to have lived up to my expectations. Being refunded was not the issue. Disappointed, and would not recomment - except for the food.Overally - Disappointing for a 5 star. But great cuisine.	
