Mar 18 2007 	English Charm	I stay at The Connaught several times a year for business. It has the typical challenges of many London hotels - rooms are small and the bathrooms antiquated. There is quite a bit of furniture crammed into the room such as a desk and chair, the bed, armoire, etc., which means that there is only enough room to carefully navigate around the bed to get to the bathroom. The furniture is always nicely cared for and the beds are always very comfortable. The bathrooms are antiquated but nice and each usually have an oversize tub with a half-glass barrier for showers and a removable shower head. The rooms are always very clean. The lobby is a bit stuffy, but the bars are more relaxed. I like to take the stairs that are in the center of the hotel, even when I am a few floors up - the elevator works well but is small even for three. The service is very good and the staff very polite. I also love the location. Expect to pay high-end London prices.	
